#c IT/Systems
#d display a deprecation warning

PKG=`basename $_dk_s7`

echo -e "\n\nWARNING:

The $PKG dotkit is deprecated. 
This can happen for two reasons:
  1) The package is old and is being 
     removed.
  2) Dotkit for package does not conform to
     dotkit naming standards and is being 
     replaced or renamed.
Please see http://webserver/dotkit-howto for
tips on finding the package you need and other
information on using dotkit in the Broad 
computing environment."

